  "root_text": {
    "an3.45:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3.45 ",
    "an3.45:0.2": "5. Cūḷavagga ",
    "an3.45:0.3": "Paṇḍitasutta ",
    "an3.45:1.1": "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, paṇḍitapaññattāni sappurisapaññattāni. ",
    "an3.45:1.2": "Katamāni tīṇi? ",
    "an3.45:1.3": "Dānaṁ, bhikkhave, paṇḍitapaññattaṁ sappurisapaññattaṁ. ",
    "an3.45:1.4": "Pabbajjā, bhikkhave, paṇḍitapaññattā sappurisapaññattā. ",
    "an3.45:1.5": "Mātāpitūnaṁ, bhikkhave, upaṭṭhānaṁ paṇḍitapaññattaṁ sappurisapaññattaṁ. ",
    "an3.45:1.6": "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi paṇḍitapaññattāni sappurisapaññattānīti. ",
    "an3.45:2.1": "Sabbhi dānaṁ upaññattaṁ, ",
    "an3.45:2.2": "ahiṁsā saṁyamo damo; ",
    "an3.45:2.3": "Mātāpitu upaṭṭhānaṁ, ",
    "an3.45:2.4": "santānaṁ brahmacārinaṁ. ",
    "an3.45:3.1": "Sataṁ etāni ṭhānāni, ",
    "an3.45:3.2": "yāni sevetha paṇḍito; ",
    "an3.45:3.3": "Ariyo dassanasampanno, ",
    "an3.45:3.4": "sa lokaṁ bhajate sivan”ti. ",
    "an3.45:3.5": "Pañcamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an3.45:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 3.45 ",
    "an3.45:0.2": "5. The Lesser Chapter ",
    "an3.45:0.3": "Recommended by the Astute ",
    "an3.45:1.1": "“Mendicants, these three things are recommended by astute true persons. ",
    "an3.45:1.2": "What three? ",
    "an3.45:1.3": "Giving, ",
    "an3.45:1.4": "going forth, ",
    "an3.45:1.5": "and taking care of your mother and father. ",
    "an3.45:1.6": "These are the three things recommended by astute true persons. ",
    "an3.45:2.1": "The virtuous recommend giving, ",
    "an3.45:2.2": "harmlessness, restraint, and self-control; ",
    "an3.45:2.3": "caring for mother and father, ",
    "an3.45:2.4": "and peaceful spiritual practitioners. ",
    "an3.45:3.1": "These are the things recommended by the good, ",
    "an3.45:3.2": "which the astute should cultivate. ",
    "an3.45:3.3": "A noble one, having vision, ",
    "an3.45:3.4": "will enjoy a world of grace.” "
  },
